<TITLE> Bangladesh climb up one step in FIFA ranking </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 20 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh climbed up one step , securing the 175th place in the FIFA ranking . Bangladesh, who had 176th position in the August ranking, secured four points after taking part in the Nehru Cup in India and Merdeka Cup in Malaysia. In both the tournaments, Bangladesh secured only one point playing a 1-1 draw against Cambodia in India. After clinching the Nehru Cup at home, India advanced six steps to hold the 145th place, top among the South Asian countries. Bangladesh ranked third out of seven South Asian countries  India (145th), Maldives (165th), Sri Lanka (166th), Bangladesh (175th), Pakistan (179th), Nepal (185th) and Bhutan (197th). 
